name: Sailthru
description: Add a Sailthru Instance to connect your existing Sailthru account to Cloud Elements.

configuration.name: Base URL
configuration.description: The base URL for your Sailthru account.

configuration.name: Sailthru API Key
configuration.description: The API Key for your Sailthru account.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Sailthru API format
configuration.description: The format for the Sailthru response.

configuration.name: Sailthru API Secret
configuration.description: The API Secret for your Sailthru account.

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Poller Refresh Interval
configuration.description: How Often to Poll for Events? (minutes)

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

configuration.name: List to Monitor
configuration.description: Which List to monitor for events?

resources.description: Search for lists to validate that the API keys are correct

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Required is `status`. Possible values for `status` =[`draft`, `scheduled`, `sending`, `sent`]. Other optional parameters to search are `list`, `start_date` and `end_date`. For Eg- `status='sent' and list='test_list'`.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. Defaults to 1 if not provided

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 20 if not provided.
